default4
default Here, spikes around the Copenhagen conference and recently, are not necessarily reassuring, as they may represent the ‘spasmodic recurrence’ of attention allowed for in this perspective. In addition, this overarching pattern cannot be looked at in isolation from the much, much larger quantity of coverage that bears on non-climate, ‘bread-and-butter’ issues, like crime, health and economics.
