defaultConclusionsdefault&#xa0;
default4
default.
default1
default              
defaultFrom 
defaultth
defaulte 
defaultperspective
default of the evidence presented here
default, the picture is concern
defaulting
default. It invites us to consider 
defaulta number of 
defaultinterrelated 
defaultissues. 
defaultTo what extent do we need a research agenda that takes into consideration the structure of climate change coverage in the widest possible range of media? Do we need to find a way to integrate existing research on climate attitudes and attitude development, with a fuller appreciation of these structures. And to what extent do the principal funders of such research need to 
defaultbe encouraged to 
defaultacknowledge 
defaultsuch 
defaultissues?
default&#xa0;
default4.2
default              
defaultIn addition, there are questions for the broadcasters
default and for the press
default. Given the remit 
defaultof the former 
defaultto educate and inform the public, h
defaultow 
defaultfar 
defaultare they prepared to 
defaultgo to 
defaultdocument 
defaultclimate 
defaultchange 
defaultin the future?
default 
defaultW
defaultill 
defaultth
defaulteir
default output reflect the urgency the scientific com
defaultmunity express about the issue
default, and will this be tempered significantly by concerns about audience figures and advertising revenue
default? 
defaultAnd t
defaulto what extent will 
defaultcounter-consensus messages like that embodied in the ‘Great Global Warming Swindle’
default be given a place in broadcasting output?
default For 
defaultnewspaper 
defaulteditors, some of the same themes emerge. Although, the press acknowledge no obligation to inform or educate the public, they should perhaps consider more fully than they do at present, the potential impact their coverage has, and the extent to which it serves the public good.
default&#xa0;
default4.3
default              
defaultFinally, what role do senior government politicians have in heightening the media profile of climate change? 
defaultThe media often take their cue on what is important from these figures. 
defaultHere
default,
default the issue of political leadership 
defaultcomes 
defaultto the forefront.
